<div id="faq-modal" class="modal">
    <div class="modal-content">
        <h4 style="text-align: center;">FAQ</h4>
        <a> <b> How can I create my own dance? </b> </a>
        <p style="color:gray"> From <b style="color:black"> Home,</b> click the <b style="color:black"> Plus </b>
            button, then enter the name of your dance and choose the song you want to upload. </p>


        <a> <b> How can I add & delete my picture, text, or audio cues?</b> </a>
        <p style="color:gray"> To add your own cues, click the <b style="color:black"> Edit </b> button on the dance of
            your choice, then add your own picture, text, or audio cues. To delete a particular cue, click the <b
                    style="color:black"> Trash </b> button beside the cue you want to remove </p>

        <a> <b> How can I go to my dance after adding the cues? </b> </a>
        <p style="color:gray"> After adding all the cues you want, click the <b style="color:black"> Play </b> button
            located at the top-right corner of the page. This will automacally lead you to your dance. </p>


        <a> <b> How can I loop the song?</b> </a>
        <p style="color:gray"> Under the <b style="color:black"> Play page, </b> you will be able to loopthe music by
            moving the two endpoints of the range slider into a particular song you want to loop. Then, toggle the <b
                    style="color:black"> Loop </b> button and your songshould be automatically playing in a loop. </p>

